&lt;p&gt;In 1973 at Xerox PARC, Bob Metcalfe sketched a way for many computers to share a single wire — borrowing the throughput math from his study of Hawaii&#39;s ALOHAnet — and he and David Boggs built it and measured it until it held. Behind Ethernet was a two-person team that turned a contested idea into the measured standard now carrying almost all the world&#39;s wired traffic.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Mercury, we’re looking to accelerate several of our AI products that our customers love like Command, CLI, and MCP.&amp;nbsp; We’re building for ambitious people of all kinds, and are a company made of founders and small technical teams trying to change the world - as part of that, we’re taking open applications for founders or small technical teams (Eng+) that want to work together on building the AI products of the future.&amp;nbsp; This isn&#39;t a fixed role. We expect the nature of work is changing, and small teams of people paired with AI product surface and autonomy to build can create 10x outcomes. Apply as a small team or as an individual &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Here are some things you’ll do on the job:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Find the problem. Work close enough to customers that you spot what matters before anyone assigns it to you — then decide it&#39;s worth building.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and automate the workflow end to end using Command, CLI, MCP, and the rest of our AI stack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ship to customers fast — quick understanding, tight iteration, deploy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure the impact honestly, then do the next one. Kill what didn&#39;t move; double down on what did.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run as an autonomous team — pick the target, ship the thing, own the outcome.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have shipped something real -&amp;nbsp; a product, a tool, a company, or an open-source project people actually use.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be dangerous across the stack: PMs who can prototype, engineers with product taste.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have strong opinions about AI products and the judgment to recognize fast when one of them is wrong.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands experience building AI products with AI, and knowledge about RAG, evals, agent harnesses a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Move fast and measure. Expect most experiments to fail and treat that as the price of finding the ones that don&#39;t.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Care about craft where it&#39;s impactful and resist polishing what isn&#39;t.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate clearly and own outcomes - we want real business impact, customer time/pain saved, and a path to scaling what works&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
