&lt;p&gt;In 1923, Claude Hopkins published Scientific Advertising, introducing early ideas around experimentation, attribution, and measurable decision-making. Behind the book was a team that meticulously designed, executed, and measured campaigns — setting the foundation for modern, data-driven growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Mercury, that mindset extends beyond marketing. It spans how we acquire customers, how we activate and convert them, and how we design product experiences that drive long-term value.&lt;/p&gt;
